Thanks! It's all still WIP since .23. Currently I have;

-the Copernicus (the massive crew transport Elo capable btw)

-the Science lander similarly shaped as the hab lander on the image

-the Hab. lander with return vehicle. This is the one I generally use for a quick mission to Duna.

To complete a proper mission I still want an additional lander with a proper command-potted 2 manned rover to move some useless gadgets around like a solar farm and some larger scientific equipment. I would love to add a atmospherical drone to it too but I am not quite sure if I can squeeze it in. To complete this mission will take a while longer I am afraid.

really good crafts in here. but why nobody has science there? on every lander i have a science jr. it's difficult to build it in in a lander but worth the try.

my newest duna lander. i was able to get back to orbit, redock with my interplanetary stage, refuel, undock, travel to ike, land, return, redock in duna orbit and went home! 4000 science because my interplanetary stage have a mobile lab with bill and bob in it.

all stock with 2x LV-909 next to the science jr.

Kegel II is balanced a little bit better, is a little lighter, and doesn't carry the now-unnecessary descent stage. It docks the other way 'round on Dewey, so it can use five engines (four as a tractor, two as pushers) and not leave any unburning. I was carrying around six engines before and only using four. Now I'm carrying five and using all of them! Duh!

So, now I can reliably land on the MÃƒÂ¼n! Next thing to do there is build a base! I'm working on some VTOL lifters to bring down hab modules.

Went to the Mun for a photo op and then returned to Kerbin orbit to dock with Space Station One. SS Hellblazer will be up in a couple days to refuel lander and switch out crew.
